                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d99">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.01/12–2448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in El Salvador</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-24T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 24, 1948—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>135. Question resumption relations El Salvador involved over-all considerations
                    raised by three revolutions.<note n="1" xml:id="d99fn1">In Peru, El Salvador,
                        and Venezuela.</note> Therefore while Dept sympathizes with your comments re
                    domestic policies new Sal Govt these not determining factors.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
